uk.co.strangeskies.reflection

Interface Scope<I>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of the enclosing instance
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ScopeImpl

    public interface Scope<I>
    Represents a static, compile-time scope for evaluation of java expressions. A scope defines which local variables are available, as well as the enclosing type of the expression (i.e. the type of the "this" reference).

    Available local variables may conceptually include method parameters of any enclosing methods or lambdas.
